│     Flask App       │
│      app.py         │
└───────┬─────┬───────┘
        │     │
        │     │
        ▼     ▼
┌──────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐
│ Amazon S3│ │ Secrets Manager │
└─────┬────┘ └────────┬────────┘
      │               │
      └──────┬────────┘
             ▼
      ┌───────────────┐
      │ AWS KMS (CMK) │
      └───────────────┘
```

---

# AWS Services Used

## Amazon S3

Stores employee onboarding documents.

Folder structure:

```text
company-onboarding-docs/
│
├── emp-0f6b206e/
│   ├── offer_letter.pdf
│   ├── nda.pdf
│   └── it_policy.pdf
│
├── emp-93237f41/
│   ├── offer_letter.pdf
│   ├── nda.pdf
│   └── it_policy.pdf
```

### Purpose
- Durable document storage
- Secure downloads
- Centralized employee records

---

## AWS KMS

Customer Managed Key:

```text
alias/onboarding-cmk
```

Used by:

- Amazon S3
- AWS Secrets Manager

### Purpose

- Encrypt employee documents
- Encrypt employee credentials
- Centralized key management
- Auditability and compliance

---

## AWS Secrets Manager

Stores:

```json
{
  "employee_id": "emp-eb619d3d",
  "email": "employee@company.com",
  "temp_password": "generated-password",
  "vpn_key": "generated-vpn-key",
  "slack_token": "generated-token",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "role": "DevOps"
}
```

### Purpose

- Secure credential storage
- Credential retrieval
- Encryption using KMS

---

# Application Workflow

## Step 1 – Employee Registration

User enters:

- First Name
- Last Name
- Email
- Department
- Role

and uploads:

- Offer Letter
- NDA
- IT Policy

---

## Step 2 – Credential Generation

Application generates:

- Temporary Password
- VPN Key
- Slack Token

Example:

```python
temp_password = base64.urlsafe_b64encode(
    os.urandom(18)
).decode()
```

---

## Step 3 – Store Credentials

Credentials stored in:

```text
Secrets Manager

onboarding/<employee-id>/credentials
```

Example:

```text
onboarding/emp-eb619d3d/credentials
```

---

## Step 4 – Upload Documents

Documents uploaded to:

```text
S3 Bucket
```

Path:

```text
emp-eb619d3d/
 ├── offer_letter.pdf
 ├── nda.pdf
 └── it_policy.pdf
```

Encryption:

```text
SSE-KMS
```

using:

```text
alias/onboarding-cmk
```

---

## Step 5 – Employee Listing

Application scans S3 bucket and displays:

```text
Employee ID
Documents
Credentials
```

---

## Step 6 – Secret Retrieval

When user clicks:

```text
Reveal Credentials
```

Application retrieves:

```python
secrets_client.get_secret_value()
```

from AWS Secrets Manager.

---

